description: Deep in the subterranean weasel stronghold of Darkheather, Saxon wakes to find himself in the horrific mass grave of his fallen Guard mice from the Winter War of 1149. In the mouse tomb he must face the cages, shackles, pelts, and bones of the past. Above on the icy surface of the mouse territories Lieam and Celanawe face the one-eyed owl as they wield sword and Black Axe against the feathered predator.

Convinced that his parents’ death wasn’t an accident, ex CIA agent Ward Hopkins is obsessed with finding the people responsible for their murder. But his investigation only uncovers more questions about his own mysterious past and his connection to the elusive STRAW MEN. Meanwhile the notorious serial killer known as the Upright Man continues to terrorize his latest victim, Sarah Becker. Will Ward be able to put all the pieces together in time to uncover the secret of the Straw Men and save Sarah from her fate at the hands of their deadliest member, the Upright Man? The clock is ticking and Sarah’s time is about to run out.
name: Chapter Three

description: The true extent of House De Kyp's treachery and corruption is about to be revealed when without warning, a huge object impacts the surface. It's a drop pad which deposits the which deposits the nightmarish juggernaut that is a Chaos Dreadnought. Tasked to wipe out both Inquisitor Alastor's team and the Damask Brothers, will Chaos reign?

Captured by the Red Fangs Dog Tribe, Michael and Abi are helpless. But aid can come in strange forms. Who is the mysterious man so interested in their welfare? What does it have to do with an impending marriage? And who will come from the city to save them?

description: In 30 Days 'til Death, Rufus is just a guy trying to fit in, to get by and not be noticed. But there's a catch; Rufus is a vampire. So why does a vampire want to keep such a low profile? Because he is being tracked by the mother of all hit squads, made up of 'old guard' vampires who don't take kindly to these punk kids and their new ways.
